criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Healthy adult (American Society of Anesthesiologists physical status 1 and 2)
             parturients at term (36 weeks gestation or more) (nulliparous and multiparous);

          -  With a singleton fetus.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Multiple pregnancies;

          -  Non-cephalic fetal presentation;

          -  Obstetric complications (e.g. pre-eclampsia, uncontrolled hypertension, uncontrolled
             diabetes);

          -  Elective and urgent caesarean section (not from delivery suite).
